source: crates/biome_html_analyze/tests/spec_tests.rs
expression: invalid.html
---
# Input
```html
<!-- should generate diagnostics -->
<button aria-hidden="true">Click me</button>
<a href="/" aria-hidden="true">link</a>
<input aria-hidden="true" />
<div tabindex="0" aria-hidden="true"></div>
<select aria-hidden="true"><option>opt</option></select>
<textarea aria-hidden="true">text</textarea>
<div contenteditable="true" aria-hidden="true">editable</div>
<p tabindex="0" aria-hidden="true">text</p>

```

# Diagnostics
```
invalid.html:2:1 lint/a11y/noAriaHiddenOnFocusable  FIXABLE  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  × Disallow aria-hidden="true" from being set on focusable elements.
  
    1 │ <!-- should generate diagnostics -->
  > 2 │ <button aria-hidden="true">Click me</button>
      │ ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
    3 │ <a href="/" aria-hidden="true">link</a>
    4 │ <input aria-hidden="true" />
  
  i aria-hidden should not be set to true on focusable elements because this can lead to confusing behavior for screen reader users.
  
  i Unsafe fix: Remove the aria-hidden attribute from the element.
  
    2 │ <button·aria-hidden="true">Click·me</button>␍
      │         ------------------                  

```

